    <item>
      <title>Interactive Semioverse</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/interactive-semioverse/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 12 Nov 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/library/relationality/domains/universes/semiotic-universe/domains/interactive-semioverse/interactive-semioverse/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;abstract&#34;&gt;Abstract&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&#34;../semiotic-universe/semiotic-universe.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;semiotic universe&lt;/a&gt; constructs a self-sustaining &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;sign&lt;/a&gt; system — a minimal structure in which everything sayable is meaningful and everything meaningful is sayable. But a sign system that only talks to itself is incomplete: &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;signs&lt;/a&gt; in the world point at things, interact with reality, fail, leave traces, and acquire or lose influence. The &lt;strong&gt;Interactive Semioverse&lt;/strong&gt; extends the semiotic universe with structures that formalize how &lt;a href=&#34;../../../../linguistics/topics/semiotics/terms/sign.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;signs&lt;/a&gt; engage with what is outside the sign system.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
